{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers\/howtocontainerizeanagent"]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers"]]},"metadata":{"title":"How to Containerize an Agent","modules":[{"name":"SwiftSynapseContainers"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials","title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerSandboxGuide","doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/SecureProductionGuide","doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/HowToUseContainerPool"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Containerizing an agent is an additive change — you add one macro and one method call. No changes to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"execute(goal:)"},{"type":"text","text":", no changes to tool registration, no changes to the Harness configuration."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Before-You-Start","text":"Before You Start","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Confirm you have:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftSynapseContainers"},{"type":"text","text":" in your "},{"code":"Package.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (replaces "},{"code":"SwiftSynapseHarness","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"container"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI installed: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"brew install container"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The target image pulled: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"container pull swift:latest"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"com.apple.security.virtualization"},{"type":"text","text":" entitlement for distribution builds"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-1-Add-Containerized","level":2,"text":"Step 1: Add @Containerized"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Place ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Containerized"},{"text":" directly above ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@SpecDrivenAgent"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Before:","@SpecDrivenAgent","public actor AnalysisAgent { ... }","","\/\/ After:","@Containerized(image: \"swift:latest\", policy: .strict)","@SpecDrivenAgent","public actor AnalysisAgent { ... }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The macro generates three members. You don’t write these — they appear automatically:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Generated by @Containerized:","public var containerConfig: ContainerConfiguration = ContainerConfiguration(","    image: \"swift:latest\",","    cpuCount: 2,","    memoryGB: 4,","    diskGB: 20,","    policy: .strict,","    networkEnabled: false,","    mounts: [],","    environment: [:],","    timeoutSeconds: 300",")","public var _containerID: String? = nil","public func containerized(goal: String) async throws -> ContainerizedResult<String> { ... }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-2-Choose-the-Right-Policy","level":2,"text":"Step 2: Choose the Right Policy"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Match ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/SandboxPolicy"},{"text":" to your trust model:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Untrusted code — no network, no mounts (safest)","@Containerized(image: \"swift:latest\", policy: .strict)","","\/\/ Trusted agent that calls an LLM API","@Containerized(image: \"swift:latest\", policy: .standard, timeoutSeconds: 120)","","\/\/ Trusted agent that needs to read input files","@Containerized(image: \"ubuntu:24.04\", policy: .permissive)","\/\/ Then add mounts to containerConfig after init if needed"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-3-Size-the-VM","level":2,"text":"Step 3: Size the VM"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cpuCount"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"memoryGB"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"diskGB"},{"text":" based on your workload. The defaults (2 vCPU, 4 GB, 20 GB) suit most LLM-calling agents:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Containerized(","    image: \"swift:latest\",","    cpuCount: 4,       \/\/ increase for compute-heavy tasks","    memoryGB: 8,       \/\/ increase if the agent loads large models or datasets","    diskGB: 40,        \/\/ increase for agents that write large files","    timeoutSeconds: 600",")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ContainerizedResult.peakMemoryBytes"},{"text":" from a test run to right-size ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"memoryGB"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-4-Call-containerizedgoal","level":2,"text":"Step 4: Call containerized(goal:)"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Switch the call site from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"run(goal:)"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"containerized(goal:)"},{"text":" for workloads that need isolation:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Harness run — hooks, permissions, and resilience apply, execute() runs in host:","let response = try await agent.run(goal: goal)","","\/\/ Containerized run — execute() runs inside the MicroVM:","let result = try await agent.containerized(goal: goal)","let output = result.value"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use both on the same actor — ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"run(goal:)"},{"text":" for trusted goals, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"containerized(goal:)"},{"text":" for untrusted ones.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-5-Handle-Container-Errors","level":2,"text":"Step 5: Handle Container Errors"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add a catch block for ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerizedAgentError"},{"text":" alongside your existing error handling:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["do {","    let result = try await agent.containerized(goal: userInput)","    return result.value","} catch ContainerizedAgentError.imageNotFound(let image) {","    throw MyError.missingImage(image)","} catch ContainerizedAgentError.timeoutExceeded(let seconds) {","    throw MyError.agentTimeout(seconds)","} catch ContainerizedAgentError.containerToolNotFound {","    throw MyError.setupRequired(\"Install container CLI: brew install container\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Complete-Example","level":2,"text":"Complete Example"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["import SwiftSynapseContainers","","@Containerized(image: \"swift:latest\", cpuCount: 2, memoryGB: 4, policy: .strict)","@SpecDrivenAgent","public actor CodeReviewAgent {","    private let config: AgentConfiguration","","    public init(configuration: AgentConfiguration) throws {","        self.config = configuration","        _ = try configuration.buildLLMClient()","    }","","    public func execute(goal: String) async throws -> String {","        let client = try config.buildLLMClient()","        let agent = Agent(client: client, model: config.modelName)","        return try await agent.respond(to: goal)","    }","}","","\/\/ Usage:","let agent = try CodeReviewAgent(configuration: config)","let result = try await agent.containerized(goal: \"Review this PR for security issues:\\n\\(prDiff)\")","print(result.value)","print(\"Ran in \\(result.wallTimeSeconds)s using \\(result.peakMemoryBytes \/ 1_048_576) MB\")"],"type":"codeListing"}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/HowToContainerizeAnAgent","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Step-by-step guide to adding ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Containerized","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to an existing ","type":"text"},{"code":"@SpecDrivenAgent","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" actor.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://SwiftSynapseContainers/documentation/SwiftSynapseContainers/GettingStarted":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/GettingStarted","title":"Getting Started with SwiftSynapseContainers","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers\/gettingstarted","kind":"article","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"From a standard SwiftSynapse agent to a hardware-isolated MicroVM agent in four steps."}]},"doc://SwiftSynapseContainers/documentation/SwiftSynapseContainers/SandboxPolicy":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SandboxPolicy"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/SandboxPolicy","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SandboxPolicy"}],"title":"SandboxPolicy","url":"\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers\/sandboxpolicy","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Controls the security posture of a MicroV